"use strict";
eval("__webpack_require__.r(__webpack_exports__);\n/* harmony export */ __webpack_require__.d(__webpack_exports__, {\n/* harmony export */   getInterpretation: () => (/* binding */ getInterpretation),\n/* harmony export */   interpretations: () => (/* binding */ interpretations)\n/* harmony export */ });\n/**\n * Interpretations for the 22 energies of the Destiny Matrix.\n * Each energy has detailed archetype descriptions, positive/negative traits, and actionable advice.\n */ const interpretations = {\n    1: {\n        number: 1,\n        name: \"The Magician\",\n        archetype: \"Willpower & Manifestation\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Leadership\",\n            \"Creativity\",\n            \"Initiative\",\n            \"Communication\",\n            \"Charisma\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Brain, nervous system, head\",\n        element: \"Air\",\n        positive: \"Strong leadership qualities and the ability to take initiative in any situation. You possess exceptional communication skills, creativity, and the power to manifest your ideas into reality. You're a natural-born communicator with magnetic energy that draws people toward you. When balanced, you inspire others through your vision and drive. You excel at starting new projects and have the entrepreneurial spirit needed to turn dreams into tangible results. Your charisma is your superpower — people are naturally drawn to your confidence and vision. You have a gift for diplomacy and can navigate complex social situations with ease.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, this energy can lead to manipulation of others, arrogance, and using your considerable talents purely for selfish purposes. You may suppress your own potential out of deep-seated fear of failure or judgment. There's a tendency to become overly controlling, wanting everything done your way. You might struggle with follow-through, starting many projects but completing few. Ego inflation can cause you to overlook the contributions and feelings of others. In its shadow form, this energy creates a person who talks much but does little, or who uses their persuasive abilities to deceive.\",\n        advice: \"Trust your inner power and creative abilities. Channel your abundant energy into meaningful creative pursuits and lead by example rather than through force or manipulation. Practice finishing what you start — your greatest growth comes from commitment. Develop genuine humility while maintaining your natural confidence. Remember that true leadership means serving others, not just commanding them. Meditate regularly to keep your mental energy focused and clear.\"\n    },\n    2: {\n        number: 2,\n        name: \"The High Priestess\",\n        archetype: \"Intuition & Inner Wisdom\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Intuition\",\n            \"Mystery\",\n            \"Patience\",\n            \"Sensitivity\",\n            \"Wisdom\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Reproductive system, hormones\",\n        element: \"Water\",\n        positive: \"You possess profound intuition and an exceptional ability to sense what lies beneath the surface. Your sensitivity allows you to understand hidden truths that others miss entirely. You're a natural counselor and confidant — people feel safe sharing their deepest secrets with you. You have a strong connection to the subconscious mind and may experience vivid dreams or psychic insights. When balanced, you combine patient wisdom with gentle strength, knowing exactly when to speak and when to remain silent. Your diplomatic skills are unmatched, and you can navigate delicate situations with grace.\",\n        negative: \"In its shadow form, this energy creates excessive passivity and chronic indecisiveness. You may become overly secretive, hiding your true feelings behind a mask of mystery. There's a tendency toward emotional manipulation — using your intuitive understanding of others to control them subtly. You might ignore your own powerful intuition out of fear or social pressure, leading to poor decisions. Overthinking and analysis paralysis can prevent you from taking necessary action. You may also struggle with codependency, losing yourself in others' emotional needs.\",\n        advice: \"Listen to your inner voice — it is one of the most powerful gifts you possess. Balance your deeply receptive nature with decisive action when the moment calls for it. Trust your gut feelings, especially when they contradict logical reasoning. Practice setting healthy boundaries while maintaining your natural empathy. Regular time alone in quiet contemplation will strengthen your intuitive abilities. Journal your dreams and intuitive hits to develop a stronger connection to your inner wisdom.\"\n    },\n    3: {\n        number: 3,\n        name: \"The Empress\",\n        archetype: \"Abundance & Creativity\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Fertility\",\n            \"Beauty\",\n            \"Nurturing\",\n            \"Nature\",\n            \"Sensuality\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Throat, thyroid, vocal cords\",\n        element: \"Earth\",\n        positive: \"You radiate nurturing energy and possess an extraordinary ability to create beauty and abundance in all its forms. Your artistic talent is innate and can manifest through any creative medium — art, music, writing, cooking, gardening, or design. You have a natural green thumb for growing things, whether plants, businesses, or relationships. When balanced, you embody the divine feminine energy of creation and sustenance. Your presence is calming and your home tends to be a sanctuary for others. You understand the cycles of nature and can work with them rather than against them. Material abundance flows easily to you when you're aligned with your creative purpose.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, this energy leads to overindulgence in sensual pleasures, smothering those you love with excessive care, and creative blocks that cause deep frustration. You may become overly dependent on material comforts or use luxury as an escape from emotional pain. There's a tendency to neglect your own needs while pouring everything into others. Jealousy and possessiveness in relationships can arise. You might struggle with body image issues or use food, shopping, or other sensual pleasures as coping mechanisms. Creative drought can lead to depression and a sense of purposelessness.\",\n        advice: \"Express your creative nature freely and without judgment — it's as essential to your well-being as breathing. Nurture others generously but never at the cost of losing yourself in the process. Create daily rituals that connect you to beauty and nature. Invest time in developing at least one creative skill to mastery. Practice receiving as gracefully as you give. Remember that your worth is not measured by what you produce or provide for others.\"\n    },\n    4: {\n        number: 4,\n        name: \"The Emperor\",\n        archetype: \"Structure & Authority\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Stability\",\n            \"Discipline\",\n            \"Logic\",\n            \"Protection\",\n            \"Order\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Spine, skeletal system, joints\",\n        element: \"Fire\",\n        positive: \"You possess natural authority and exceptional organizational skills that create stability and order wherever you go. Your discipline and work ethic are remarkable — you can build lasting structures, systems, and organizations from the ground up. You're a natural protector who takes responsibility seriously. When balanced, you provide the kind of steady, reliable leadership that others depend on. You think strategically and can see the long-term consequences of decisions. Your ability to create order from chaos is a superpower in business and family life alike. You value tradition and honor, and you build your life on a foundation of integrity.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, rigidity and controlling behavior dominate your interactions. You may become stubbornly resistant to change, even when it's clearly necessary. Fear of vulnerability can make you emotionally distant and cold. There's a tendency toward authoritarian leadership, demanding obedience rather than inspiring cooperation. You might become a workaholic, defining your entire self-worth through achievement and status. Micromanaging others and refusing to delegate reveals a deep lack of trust. Emotional suppression can lead to anger outbursts or health problems related to stress.\",\n        advice: \"Build strong, lasting foundations in every area of your life, but remain flexible enough to adapt when circumstances change. True power comes from wisdom and compassion, not from control and domination. Practice vulnerability with trusted people — it's not weakness, it's courage. Learn to delegate and trust others' capabilities. Balance your drive for achievement with presence and emotional availability for your loved ones. Remember that the strongest structures in nature are those that can bend without breaking.\"\n    },\n    5: {\n        number: 5,\n        name: \"The Hierophant\",\n        archetype: \"Wisdom & Teaching\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Tradition\",\n            \"Knowledge\",\n            \"Mentorship\",\n            \"Spirituality\",\n            \"Education\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Ears, respiratory system\",\n        element: \"Earth\",\n        positive: \"You carry deep spiritual wisdom and an extraordinary ability to teach and mentor others. You understand complex systems of belief, philosophy, and tradition, and can translate them into practical guidance. When balanced, you bridge the gap between ancient wisdom and modern life. You're a natural educator who can make complex concepts accessible to anyone. Your presence brings a sense of sacred order and meaning to everyday life. You value both learning and sharing knowledge, creating a cycle of wisdom that benefits communities.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, this energy creates dogmatism and rigid adherence to rules without understanding their purpose. You may become preachy, imposing your beliefs on others without respecting their autonomy. There's a tendency toward blind conformity or, conversely, complete rejection of all tradition. Spiritual bypass — using spiritual concepts to avoid dealing with real-world problems — is a common shadow. You might use your position of knowledge to feel superior to others.\",\n        advice: \"Share your knowledge generously and without attachment to being 'right.' Find the golden balance between honoring valuable traditions and discovering your own personal truth. Be a guide, not a guru — empower others to find their own wisdom rather than making them dependent on yours. Stay curious and remain a student even as you teach. Practice what you preach consistently.\"\n    },\n    6: {\n        number: 6,\n        name: \"The Lovers\",\n        archetype: \"Love & Choices\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Partnership\",\n            \"Harmony\",\n            \"Values\",\n            \"Beauty\",\n            \"Duality\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Heart, circulatory system\",\n        element: \"Air\",\n        positive: \"You have a profound capacity for deep, meaningful love and harmonious relationships. Your ability to make heart-centered choices guides you toward authentic connections. When balanced, you create beauty and harmony in every relationship and environment you touch. You understand that love is a choice made daily, not just a feeling. Your natural charm and warmth attract genuine connections. You value loyalty, partnership, and the sacred bond between souls. You have an innate sense of aesthetics and can create beauty in your surroundings.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, codependency and inability to make decisions plague your relationships. You may stay in unhealthy situations out of fear of being alone. Superficial relationships that lack depth and authenticity become a pattern. Fear of commitment can lead to a series of shallow connections. You might sacrifice your own values and identity to maintain harmony, losing yourself in the process. Jealousy, comparison, and romantic idealization can create suffering.\",\n        advice: \"Follow your heart in all major decisions while keeping your mind as a wise advisor. Build relationships based on mutual respect, authenticity, and shared values rather than need or fear. Practice loving yourself first — you cannot pour from an empty cup. Make choices that align with your deepest values, even when they're difficult. Remember that true harmony includes honest communication, not just the absence of conflict.\"\n    },\n    7: {\n        number: 7,\n        name: \"The Chariot\",\n        archetype: \"Determination & Victory\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Willpower\",\n            \"Achievement\",\n            \"Focus\",\n            \"Travel\",\n            \"Ambition\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Shoulders, arms, hands\",\n        element: \"Water\",\n        positive: \"You possess extraordinary willpower, determination, and the drive to succeed through focused effort. Self-discipline comes naturally to you, and you can overcome obstacles that would stop most people. When balanced, you channel your powerful drive toward meaningful goals and achieve remarkable results. You're excellent at strategic planning and can maintain laser focus on your objectives. Travel and new experiences fuel your growth. Your success inspires others to push beyond their own limitations.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, aggressive ambition and ruthless competition dominate your behavior. You may become unable to relax, always pushing toward the next goal without enjoying your achievements. Using force instead of strategy wastes your energy and damages relationships. Burnout is a constant risk. You might become a controlling micromanager who can't trust others to do things properly. Road rage, impatience, and frustration with slower-paced people are common shadow expressions.\",\n        advice: \"Direct your powerful drive with clarity, purpose, and compassion. Victory comes through aligned, strategic action — not through brute force. Learn to celebrate achievements before immediately chasing the next goal. Balance your ambitious nature with moments of stillness and gratitude. Remember that the journey matters as much as the destination. Practice patience with others who move at a different pace.\"\n    },\n    8: {\n        number: 8,\n        name: \"Strength\",\n        archetype: \"Inner Strength & Courage\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Courage\",\n            \"Patience\",\n            \"Compassion\",\n            \"Resilience\",\n            \"Gentleness\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Heart, immune system, blood\",\n        element: \"Fire\",\n        positive: \"You embody the paradox of gentle power — your greatest strength lies not in force but in compassion, patience, and inner resilience. You have the courage to face your inner demons with love rather than aggression. When balanced, you can tame any situation through calm confidence and emotional intelligence. Your patience is remarkable, and you understand that lasting change comes through persistent gentle effort. You inspire others through your quiet strength and unwavering presence in difficult times. You have a natural ability to calm others and create safety in chaotic situations.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, deep self-doubt and cowardice prevent you from standing up for yourself or others. Suppressed anger can build up and explode in destructive ways. You might use your strength to dominate others rather than to protect and uplift them. Passive-aggressive behavior replaces honest confrontation. You may struggle with chronic people-pleasing, unable to assert your own needs. Physical health problems related to suppressed emotions are common.\",\n        advice: \"Your greatest strength is gentleness combined with unwavering courage. Face challenges with both compassion and determination. Learn to express anger constructively rather than suppressing or exploding. Stand firm in your boundaries while remaining kind. Practice self-compassion — treat yourself with the same gentleness you offer others. Physical activity, especially practices like martial arts or yoga, can help channel this energy productively.\"\n    },\n    9: {\n        number: 9,\n        name: \"The Hermit\",\n        archetype: \"Solitude & Inner Search\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Wisdom\",\n            \"Introspection\",\n            \"Guidance\",\n            \"Solitude\",\n            \"Truth\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Nervous system, intestines\",\n        element: \"Earth\",\n        positive: \"You possess profound inner wisdom gained through deep introspection and spiritual seeking. Your ability to find truth within yourself is a rare and valuable gift. Independence is natural to you, and solitude is where you recharge and access your deepest insights. When balanced, you serve as a beacon of wisdom for others while maintaining healthy boundaries. Your analytical mind can penetrate surface appearances to find deeper truths. You have the gift of discernment and can separate genuine wisdom from superficial knowledge.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, isolation and loneliness replace healthy solitude. Excessive withdrawal from the world prevents you from sharing your gifts and building meaningful connections. Fear of vulnerability keeps others at arm's length. You may become cynical, critical, or condescending toward those you perceive as less wise. Analysis paralysis prevents action. You might use your need for solitude as an excuse to avoid intimacy and responsibility.\",\n        advice: \"Honor your deep need for solitude and contemplation — it is your source of power. But remember that wisdom kept entirely to yourself helps no one. Find the balance between inner retreat and outer engagement. Share your light with the world through teaching, writing, or mentoring. Build a small circle of deep, authentic relationships rather than seeking many shallow ones. Trust that your unique perspective is needed by the world.\"\n    },\n    10: {\n        number: 10,\n        name: \"Wheel of Fortune\",\n        archetype: \"Cycles & Destiny\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Change\",\n            \"Luck\",\n            \"Karma\",\n            \"Cycles\",\n            \"Opportunity\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Metabolism, digestive system\",\n        element: \"Fire\",\n        positive: \"You have a natural understanding of life's cycles and an exceptional ability to adapt to change. Good fortune tends to follow you, especially when you align with the natural flow of events. When balanced, you ride the waves of change with grace and confidence. You understand that what goes up must come down, and what falls will rise again. Your adaptability is your greatest asset. You have an intuitive sense of timing that helps you seize opportunities at exactly the right moment.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, a gambling mentality replaces strategic thinking. You may become fatalistic, believing everything is predetermined and effort is pointless. Resistance to necessary change creates stagnation and suffering. Blaming fate or luck for personal choices removes accountability. You might become addicted to risk-taking or constantly chasing the next big break rather than building steady foundations. Instability and inconsistency in relationships and career become patterns.\",\n        advice: \"Embrace life's cycles with trust and equanimity. What goes down will surely rise again. Stay centered and grounded through all changes. Develop both patience for slow periods and readiness for opportunities. Take responsibility for your choices while remaining open to unexpected blessings. Build stable foundations that can withstand life's inevitable storms.\"\n    },\n    11: {\n        number: 11,\n        name: \"Justice\",\n        archetype: \"Balance & Truth\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Fairness\",\n            \"Truth\",\n            \"Law\",\n            \"Accountability\",\n            \"Balance\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Kidneys, adrenal glands\",\n        element: \"Air\",\n        positive: \"You have an unwavering commitment to fairness, truth, and balanced judgment. Your integrity is your cornerstone, and you can see all sides of any situation with remarkable clarity. When balanced, you bring justice and accountability wherever you go. You make excellent mediators, lawyers, judges, or advisors. Your analytical mind can weigh complex situations objectively. You value honesty above comfort and will speak truth even when it's difficult to hear.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, harsh judgment and self-righteousness dominate your interactions. You may become unable to forgive, holding grudges that poison your own well-being. Perfectionism creates impossible standards for yourself and others. You might avoid accountability while demanding it from everyone else. Black-and-white thinking prevents you from seeing nuance and gray areas. Cold, detached analysis replaces empathy and compassion.\",\n        advice: \"Seek truth and fairness in all your dealings, but start with being rigorously honest with yourself. Practice forgiveness as a form of justice for your own soul. Balance your analytical mind with compassion and understanding. Remember that justice without mercy is cruelty, and mercy without justice is weakness. Strive for fairness, not perfection. Allow others the same grace you need for yourself.\"\n    },\n    12: {\n        number: 12,\n        name: \"The Hanged Man\",\n        archetype: \"Surrender & New Perspective\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Sacrifice\",\n            \"Patience\",\n            \"Enlightenment\",\n            \"Release\",\n            \"Perspective\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Lymphatic system, feet\",\n        element: \"Water\",\n        positive: \"You possess the rare ability to see things from completely different perspectives, often finding wisdom where others see only confusion. Your willingness to sacrifice for a higher purpose gives your life deep meaning. When balanced, you understand that sometimes the most powerful action is to pause, surrender, and see from a new angle. Patience is your superpower. You can endure difficulty with grace because you trust the larger process. Your unconventional thinking leads to breakthrough insights that others miss entirely.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, martyrdom and victimhood replace genuine sacrifice. You may become stuck in stagnation, unable to take practical action because you're always 'waiting for a sign.' Chronic indecisiveness and passivity prevent progress. You might use spirituality as an excuse to avoid dealing with practical realities. Feeling perpetually misunderstood can lead to isolation and self-pity. You may sacrifice yourself needlessly, confusing suffering with spiritual growth.\",\n        advice: \"Sometimes the greatest action is to pause and see from a completely new angle. Surrender control to gain wisdom, but don't confuse surrender with giving up. Learn to distinguish genuine spiritual patience from procrastination. Take practical steps toward your goals while maintaining trust in divine timing. Practice standing on your head (literally or figuratively) to shift your perspective when stuck.\"\n    },\n    13: {\n        number: 13,\n        name: \"Death\",\n        archetype: \"Transformation & Rebirth\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Transformation\",\n            \"Endings\",\n            \"Renewal\",\n            \"Release\",\n            \"Rebirth\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Reproductive system, elimination\",\n        element: \"Water\",\n        positive: \"You possess extraordinary power of transformation and the courage to let go of what no longer serves your growth. Renewal comes naturally to you — you can reinvent yourself completely when needed. When balanced, you understand that every ending births a new beginning. You're not afraid of change; you welcome it as a catalyst for evolution. Your ability to release the past is a gift that keeps you perpetually fresh and evolving. You help others navigate their own transitions with your understanding and acceptance of life's cycles.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, deep fear of change and clinging to the past prevent necessary evolution. Destructive tendencies may manifest as you unconsciously try to force endings that aren't ready to happen. Resisting natural endings creates suffering and stagnation. You might become obsessed with control, trying to prevent the inevitable changes that life requires. Depression can result from refusing to let go of outdated identities or relationships.\",\n        advice: \"Embrace endings as doorways to new beginnings. Your power lies in your ability to transform and reinvent yourself. Don't resist the natural cycles of death and rebirth that operate in every area of life. Practice releasing attachments to outcomes, relationships, and identities that have served their purpose. Trust that what comes next will be even more aligned with your true self.\"\n    },\n    14: {\n        number: 14,\n        name: \"Temperance\",\n        archetype: \"Balance & Moderation\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Harmony\",\n            \"Healing\",\n            \"Patience\",\n            \"Integration\",\n            \"Flow\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Liver, blood circulation\",\n        element: \"Fire\",\n        positive: \"You embody the art of balance, harmony, and the integration of opposites. Your patience and moderation create sustainable success in every area of life. When balanced, you have remarkable healing abilities — whether through conventional medicine, energy work, or simply your calming presence. You understand the alchemical process of blending different elements into something greater than the sum of its parts. Your steady, flowing approach to life creates lasting harmony.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, you swing between extremes — overindulgence and deprivation, action and paralysis, engagement and withdrawal. Impatience replaces your natural steadiness. Inability to find middle ground creates constant instability. Excessive compromise might lead you to lose your own identity and values. You may become complacent, using 'balance' as an excuse for mediocrity and avoiding necessary confrontation.\",\n        advice: \"Practice the art of balance in everything — work and rest, giving and receiving, speaking and listening. The middle path often leads to the greatest fulfillment and sustainable success. Develop your natural healing abilities through study and practice. Remember that true balance is dynamic, not static — it requires constant small adjustments, not rigid adherence to a fixed position.\"\n    },\n    15: {\n        number: 15,\n        name: \"The Devil\",\n        archetype: \"Shadow & Liberation\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Shadow\",\n            \"Temptation\",\n            \"Power\",\n            \"Freedom\",\n            \"Material mastery\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Sexual organs, hormones\",\n        element: \"Earth\",\n        positive: \"You possess a deep understanding of the shadow self and the material world. Your charisma, humor, and earthly wisdom make you magnetic and influential. When balanced, you've integrated your shadow, giving you power, authenticity, and freedom from shame. You understand that acknowledging darkness is the path to genuine light. Material mastery comes naturally — you know how to create wealth and enjoy earthly pleasures without being enslaved by them. Your honest acceptance of human nature makes you an excellent psychologist, healer, or leader.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, addiction, toxic attachments, and manipulation dominate your life. Materialism replaces genuine fulfillment. You may become controlled by your desires rather than mastering them. Denial of your shadow creates projection — seeing your own flaws in everyone else while remaining blind to them in yourself. Power games in relationships cause deep suffering. Excessive sensual indulgence becomes a substitute for genuine emotional connection.\",\n        advice: \"Face your shadows with courage and compassion — they hold your greatest power. True freedom comes from acknowledging and integrating all parts of yourself, especially the ones you'd rather hide. Develop a healthy relationship with pleasure, power, and material success. Use your understanding of human desire and motivation to help rather than manipulate others. Regular shadow work and honest self-reflection are essential practices for this energy.\"\n    },\n    16: {\n        number: 16,\n        name: \"The Tower\",\n        archetype: \"Breakthrough & Awakening\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Sudden change\",\n            \"Liberation\",\n            \"Truth\",\n            \"Awakening\",\n            \"Destruction\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Muscles, teeth, sudden injuries\",\n        element: \"Fire\",\n        positive: \"You carry the energy of sudden insight, breakthrough, and liberation from false structures. When balanced, you have the courage to tear down what isn't working and rebuild something better. Your honesty is radical and refreshing. You see through pretense and illusion instantly. Breakthrough moments define your life — sudden flashes of understanding that change everything. You're a revolutionary spirit who helps others break free from limitations they didn't even know they had.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, catastrophic thinking and destructiveness without purpose create chaos in your life and the lives of those around you. You may resist necessary change until the pressure builds to explosive levels. Dramatic upheavals in relationships, career, and living situations become a recurring pattern. You might unconsciously sabotage stability because part of you believes that only through crisis can growth occur. Anger and aggression may be poorly managed.\",\n        advice: \"When structures fall, trust that something better and more authentic is being built. Breakthroughs often require breakdowns — but you can learn to initiate conscious transformation rather than waiting for crisis to force change. Channel your revolutionary energy constructively. Build resilience and flexibility so that inevitable changes feel less catastrophic. Practice grounding techniques and develop emotional regulation skills.\"\n    },\n    17: {\n        number: 17,\n        name: \"The Star\",\n        archetype: \"Hope & Inspiration\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Hope\",\n            \"Inspiration\",\n            \"Healing\",\n            \"Creativity\",\n            \"Vision\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Nervous system, skin\",\n        element: \"Air\",\n        positive: \"You are a beacon of hope and inspiration for everyone around you. Your spiritual connection is genuine and profound, and your creativity flows from a place of deep inner alignment. When balanced, you have remarkable healing abilities and can help others recover from trauma and despair. Your vision of what's possible inspires people to reach for their highest potential. You possess natural artistic talent and an aesthetic sense that creates beauty wherever you go. Your optimism is not naive — it comes from a genuine understanding of life's larger purpose.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, unrealistic expectations lead to crushing disappointment. You may become disconnected from practical reality, living in a fantasy world of possibilities that never materialize. Loss of hope and meaning can create deep depression and cynicism. You might scatter your energy across too many creative projects without completing any. Spiritual narcissism — believing you're more enlightened than others — is a shadow risk.\",\n        advice: \"You are a beacon of hope — own that role fully and share your vision generously. Trust in the universe's plan while taking practical steps toward your dreams. Stay grounded even as you reach for the stars. Complete your creative projects — your gifts need tangible expression to inspire others. Balance your spiritual awareness with practical engagement in the material world.\"\n    },\n    18: {\n        number: 18,\n        name: \"The Moon\",\n        archetype: \"Intuition & Illusion\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Intuition\",\n            \"Dreams\",\n            \"Subconscious\",\n            \"Mystery\",\n            \"Psychic ability\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Brain, mental health, fluids\",\n        element: \"Water\",\n        positive: \"You possess deep psychic abilities, a rich imagination, and profound emotional depth. Your connection to the unconscious mind gives you access to wisdom that transcends rational understanding. When balanced, you can navigate uncertainty with intuition as your compass. Your dream life is vivid and meaningful. You have a natural talent for psychology, art, music, and any field that requires understanding the hidden depths of human experience. Your emotional intelligence is exceptional.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, deception, confusion, and anxiety cloud your judgment. Fear of the unknown can paralyze you. You may become lost in illusions — either deceiving others or deceiving yourself about reality. Mood swings, anxiety, and irrational fears can dominate your experience. You might struggle to distinguish between genuine intuition and fear-based projection. Escapism through fantasy, substances, or unhealthy relationships is a common shadow pattern.\",\n        advice: \"Navigate life's uncertainties with your intuition as your guide. Not everything needs to be understood logically — sometimes feeling your way through is the wisest approach. Develop practices that help you distinguish between genuine intuition and anxiety. Regular dreamwork, journaling, and creative expression will help process the deep emotional currents you experience. Seek professional support if anxiety or mood swings become overwhelming.\"\n    },\n    19: {\n        number: 19,\n        name: \"The Sun\",\n        archetype: \"Joy & Vitality\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Joy\",\n            \"Success\",\n            \"Vitality\",\n            \"Confidence\",\n            \"Radiance\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Heart, eyes, vitality\",\n        element: \"Fire\",\n        positive: \"You radiate warmth, joy, and success wherever you go. Your natural vitality and optimism are contagious, and you have the ability to light up any room simply by walking in. When balanced, you bring genuine happiness and creative energy to everything you touch. Children and playful spirits are naturally drawn to your sunny disposition. Your confidence inspires others to shine brighter. Success comes to you more easily than most because your positive energy attracts opportunities and allies.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, ego inflation and burnout are constant risks. You may pursue superficial happiness while avoiding deeper emotions that need attention. Inability to deal with darker emotions — sadness, grief, anger — can create a forced cheerfulness that feels hollow. You might become dependent on external validation and attention. Overcommitting your energy leads to exhaustion. Your need to be the center of attention can overshadow others and damage relationships.\",\n        advice: \"Shine your light authentically and without apology — the world needs your joy. But honor your deeper emotions too; even the sun sets every day. Balance your radiant outer expression with genuine inner work. Allow yourself to have quiet, reflective moments without feeling like you're losing your spark. Share the spotlight generously and celebrate others' successes as enthusiastically as your own.\"\n    },\n    20: {\n        number: 20,\n        name: \"Judgement\",\n        archetype: \"Calling & Renewal\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Awakening\",\n            \"Purpose\",\n            \"Forgiveness\",\n            \"Renewal\",\n            \"Calling\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Blood, circulation, regeneration\",\n        element: \"Fire\",\n        positive: \"You have a powerful higher calling and the capacity for profound spiritual awakening. Your ability to forgive — yourself and others — is a transformative gift. When balanced, you hear and answer your soul's true purpose with courage and conviction. Renewal and rebirth are constant themes in your life, and each cycle brings you closer to your authentic self. You can help others find their calling through your example and guidance. Your judgment is tempered with compassion and wisdom.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, harsh self-judgment and inability to forgive create suffering and stagnation. You may ignore your calling out of fear, living a life that feels meaningless or inauthentic. Harsh criticism of others — projecting your own unresolved guilt — damages relationships. You might become frozen in the past, unable to move forward because of shame or regret. Religious or spiritual rigidity can replace genuine spiritual experience.\",\n        advice: \"Answer your higher calling with courage and faith, even when the path is unclear. Forgive the past completely — not for others' sake, but for your own freedom. Step boldly into your renewed purpose. Practice self-forgiveness daily; you are human and mistakes are part of growth. Listen for the subtle inner voice that guides you toward your true purpose, and follow it even when it requires sacrifice.\"\n    },\n    21: {\n        number: 21,\n        name: \"The World\",\n        archetype: \"Completion & Fulfillment\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Completion\",\n            \"Integration\",\n            \"Travel\",\n            \"Achievement\",\n            \"Wholeness\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Whole body integration, skin\",\n        element: \"Earth\",\n        positive: \"You embody wholeness, accomplishment, and the integration of all life's lessons into a unified wisdom. Your global perspective and love of travel expand your consciousness continually. When balanced, you have mastered the art of completing cycles and celebrating achievements before beginning new ones. Your life has a sense of completeness and fulfillment that inspires others. You can see the big picture while appreciating the small details. Cross-cultural understanding and diplomatic skill come naturally.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, a persistent feeling of incompletion prevents you from enjoying your achievements. You may fear finishing things because endings trigger anxiety. Inability to celebrate success leads to an endless cycle of striving without satisfaction. Stagnation sets in when you refuse to close chapters. You might become scattered, trying to do everything and be everywhere, without depth in any area.\",\n        advice: \"Celebrate your completions fully and prepare for new cycles with excitement rather than fear. You are more whole than you realize. Practice gratitude for how far you've come before focusing on where you're going next. Travel and cross-cultural experiences will accelerate your growth. Embrace the paradox that completion is not an end but a doorway to the next adventure.\"\n    },\n    22: {\n        number: 22,\n        name: \"The Fool\",\n        archetype: \"Freedom & New Beginnings\",\n        keywords: [\n            \"Freedom\",\n            \"Innocence\",\n            \"Adventure\",\n            \"Trust\",\n            \"Unlimited potential\"\n        ],\n        bodyArea: \"Legs, movement, freedom of body\",\n        element: \"Air\",\n        positive: \"You carry the energy of unlimited potential, freedom, and the courage to begin anew. Your spontaneity and trust in life create magical synchronicities and adventures. When balanced, you approach each day with fresh eyes and an open heart, unburdened by past failures or future anxieties. Your childlike wonder and enthusiasm are infectious. You have the rare gift of being fully present in each moment. Risk-taking comes naturally, and your willingness to leap into the unknown often leads to extraordinary experiences and growth.\",\n        negative: \"When out of balance, recklessness and naivety replace healthy spontaneity. Irresponsibility and lack of commitment create instability. Fear of taking the first step — paradoxically the opposite extreme — can also manifest. You might use 'freedom' as an excuse to avoid responsibility, commitment, and the deeper work of building something lasting. Chronic restlessness prevents you from developing depth in any area. You may repeat the same mistakes because you refuse to learn from experience.\",\n        advice: \"Embrace new beginnings with an open heart and a spirit of adventure. Your greatest adventures start with a single brave step into the unknown. Balance your love of freedom with enough structure to channel your unlimited potential into tangible results. Trust life's process while taking responsibility for your choices. Every ending is actually a new beginning in disguise — and you are the master of beginnings.\"\n    }\n};\nfunction getInterpretation(num) {\n    return interpretations[num] || interpretations[1];\n}\n//# sourceURL=[module]\n//# sourceMappingURL=data:application/json;charset=utf-8;base64,\n//# sourceURL=webpack-internal:///(ssr)/./src/lib/matrixInterpretations.ts\n");

